%section#speakers.body-section--content
  %h2 Speakers

  %div.grid
    %div.grid__cell.speaker
      %h3.speaker__name Promise Chukwuenyem
      %div.speaker__bio
        %p
          Promise Chukwuenyem is a DevOps and Ruby on Rails Engineer at
          %a(href="https://www.venturegardengroup.com/" target="_blank") Venture Garden Group.  
          He loves automating software delivery/deployment processes 
          and finds joy building solutions using Ruby on Rails. He is a very active 
          contributor on 
          %a(href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/10907864/promise-preston" target="_blank")StackOverflow 
          and often shares his knowledge in writing on 
          %a(href="https://medium.com/@promisepreston" target="_blank")Medium. 
          He also tweets a lot about his interests on 
          %a(href="https://twitter.com/PromisePreston" target="_blank")Twitter. |  
          %a(href="https://medium.com/@promisepreston" target="_blank")
            %img(src="/images/Medium.svg" height="32" alt="Medium")
          %a(href="https://stackoverflow.com/users/10907864/promise-preston" target="_blank")
            %img(src="/images/drawing.svg" height="32" alt="stackoverflow")
          %a(href="https://twitter.com/PromisePreston" target="_blank")
            %img(src="/images/Twitter.svg" height="32" alt="Twitter")


    %div.grid__cell.speaker
      %h3.speaker__name Kalebu Jordan
      %div.speaker__bio
        %p
          Kalebu Gwalugano, scientist by passion, mechatronics engineer by 
          profession, has recently found a new life in programming. It's 
          like you're little lab where you create your own little world 
          and make your own rules, it works like magic! |
          %a(href="https://kalebujordan.dev/" target="_blank")
            %img(src="/images/www.svg" height="32" alt="Web")

    %div.grid__cell.speaker
      %h3.speaker__name Brooke Kuhlmann
      %div.speaker__bio
        %p
          Brooke Kuhlmann has been a software engineer for over two decades 
          and enjoys sharing the love and craft of software engineering -- 
          especially Ruby -- via the 
          %a(href="https://www.alchemists.io/" target="_blank") Alchemists collective 
          where he 
          %a(href="https://www.alchemists.io/articles" target="_blank") writes,
          %a(href="https://www.alchemists.io/presentations" target="_blank") speaks,  
          %a(href="https://www.alchemists.io/screencasts" target="_blank") teaches, 
          and contributes to 
          %a(href="https://www.alchemists.io/projects/" target="_blank") open source software.
          %a(href="https://www.alchemists.io" target="_blank") 
            %img(src="/images/www.svg" height="32" alt="Web")

    %div.grid__cell.speaker
      %h3.speaker__name Marylene Sawyer
      %div.speaker__bio
        %p
          Mrs. Marylene Sawyer is a wife and mother who enjoys solving problems 
          and building interesting solutions through coding whenever she finds 
          time. Mrs. Sawyer is a professional full-stack software engineer currently 
          based in South Africa. She recently completed the software development 
          program at Microverse, a school for remote developers. |
          Marylene also holds a BSc in Computer Science from the University of the 
          People, Pasadena, California. |
          %a(href="http://www.marylene.tech/" target="_blank") 
            %img(src="/images/www.svg" height="32" alt="Web") 
          %a(href="https://github.com/Bluette1" target="_blank") 
            %img(src="/images/GitHub.png" height="32" alt="GitHub")

    %div.grid__cell.speaker
      %h3.speaker__name Clemence Sedem
      %div.speaker__bio
        %p
          Clemence Sedem Agozi is a software engineer and cyber security researcher.
          He is currently working at 
          %a(href="https://www.getinnotized.com/" target="_blank") getINNOtized GmbH 
          as an associate software engineer. |
          %a(href="https://github.com/clemsedem" target="_blank") 
            %img(src="/images/GitHub.png" height="32" alt="GitHub")
